<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<title>scellrun — scRNA integrate report</title>
<style>
  body { font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif; max-width: 980px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 0 1rem; color: #222; line-height: 1.55; }
  h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; border-bottom: 2px solid #333; padding-bottom: .3rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin: .5rem 0 1.5rem; font-size: .92rem; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: .35rem .55rem; text-align: right; }
  th:first-child, td:first-child { text-align: left; }
  thead { background: #f6f6f6; }
  .kv { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: .25rem .8rem; margin: .5rem 0 1rem; }
  .kv dt { color: #666; }
  img.umap { max-width: 100%; height: auto; margin: .5rem 0 1.5rem; border: 1px solid #eee; padding: .5rem; }
  .rationale { background: #fafaf6; border-left: 3px solid #c7b07a; padding: .6rem .9rem; margin: .6rem 0; font-size: .92rem; }
  .rationale strong { color: #5a4710; }
  footer { color: #888; font-size: .82rem; margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: .7rem; }
  code { background: #f0f0f0; padding: .05rem .3rem; border-radius: 3px; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h1>scRNA-seq integration report</h1>

<h2>Summary</h2>
<dl class="kv">
  <dt>Cells in</dt>          <dd>{{ "{:,}".format(result.n_cells_in) }}</dd>
  <dt>Cells used (post-QC)</dt><dd>{{ "{:,}".format(result.n_cells_used) }}</dd>
  <dt>Integration method</dt><dd>{{ result.method }}</dd>
  <dt>Sample key</dt>        <dd>{{ result.sample_key or "(none — single-batch run)" }}</dd>
  <dt>PCA dimensions</dt>    <dd>{{ result.n_pcs }}</dd>
  <dt>Cell cycle regressed</dt><dd>{{ result.cc_regressed }}</dd>
</dl>

<h2>Clusters per resolution + quality</h2>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>resolution</th><th>n_clusters</th>
      <th>largest %</th><th>smallest %</th>
      <th>singletons (&lt;2%)</th>
      <th>mixing entropy</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for res, q in quality.items() %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ res }}</td>
      <td>{{ q.n_clusters }}</td>
      <td>{{ "%.1f"|format(q.largest_pct) }}%</td>
      <td>{{ "%.1f"|format(q.smallest_pct) }}%</td>
      <td>{{ q.n_singletons }}</td>
      <td>{% if q.mixing_entropy == q.mixing_entropy %}{{ "%.2f"|format(q.mixing_entropy) }}{% else %}n/a{% endif %}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
<p style="font-size:.85rem; color:#666;">
  <em>Largest cluster &gt; 40% often means resolution too low (main population not split).
  Singleton count high (&lt;2% clusters) means resolution may be fragmenting noise.
  Mixing entropy near 1 = batches integrated well.</em>
</p>

{% if ai_rec %}
<div class="rationale" style="background:#eff5e9; border-left-color:#5a8;">
  <strong>AI recommendation:</strong> resolution = {{ ai_rec.recommended_resolution }}<br>
  <span style="font-size:.92rem;">{{ ai_rec.rationale }}</span><br>
  <span style="font-size:.78rem; color:#777;">(model suggestion — sanity-check against the table above; you make the final call)</span>
</div>
{% endif %}

<h2>UMAP grid</h2>
<img class="umap" src="{{ umap_grid_filename }}" alt="UMAP per resolution">

<h2>Cluster size distribution</h2>
<img class="umap" src="{{ sizes_filename }}" alt="Cluster sizes per resolution">
<p style="font-size:.85rem; color:#666;">
  Shows how cells distribute across clusters at each resolution. A long tail of
  tiny clusters at the right edge usually means the resolution is too high.
</p>

<div class="rationale">
  <strong>Reading the grid:</strong> the same UMAP layout, colored by cluster
  assignment at each resolution. As resolution increases, the same cells split
  into more clusters. Lower resolutions are usually the right starting point
  for biology — pick the resolution where each cluster is interpretable from
  its top markers.
</div>

{% if ratio_filename %}
<h2>Cluster × sample contingency</h2>
<p>
  Saved alongside this report as <code>{{ ratio_filename }}</code>. If a
  cluster only contains one sample's cells, integration may not have fully
  mixed batches — inspect that cluster's markers and consider a different
  integration method or sample key.
</p>
{% endif %}

<h2>Next step</h2>
<p>
  Load <code>integrated.h5ad</code> in scanpy. Use <code>obs['leiden_res_X']</code>
  to subset by cluster. v0.3 <code>scellrun scrna markers</code> will compute
  per-cluster differential markers for each resolution.
</p>

<footer>
  Generated by scellrun. Defaults reflect a clinician-bioinformatics
  working practice; substitute your own when domain demands.
</footer>

</body>
</html>
